1.
Problem: 
Notepad++ is not coming on Ubuntu right click context menu:
	I copied notepad++.desktop from /home/saumyadip/.local/share/applications/wine/Programs
	and paste it /home/saumyadip/.local/share/applications/ here 
	
	Launch with wine loader
	Solved.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
2. 
Problem: Input Signal Out Of Range
            Change Settings to 1366x768 60Hz
          
Solution:
Boot computer from safe mode (press f8 while booting)
open msconfig from run.
go to boot menu and select "Base Video" 
restart.
All done.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.
After running "rpm -e --nodeps python" yum is not working centos 6.9
Problem:
 while type yum on terminal it says: -bash: /usr/bin/yum: /usr/bin/python: bad interpreter: no such file or directory

Solution: Download
wget http://mirror.centos.org/centos/6.9/os/x86_64/Packages/python-2.6.6-66.el6_8.x86_64.rpm
rpm -ivh python-2.6.6-66.el6_8.x86_64.rpm
type yum on terminal will shows yum options..
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
